On July 14, 2020, President Biden declared a national emergency in response to the situation in Hong Kong. This was done pursuant to the International Emergency Economic Powers Act. The President stated that the actions taken by China to undermine Hong Kong's autonomy posed a threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. Therefore, the national emergency declared in 2020 will continue beyond July 14, 2022, for another year. This notice has been published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.